The paper studies logit dynamics for strategic games, which is a topic in game theory (cs.GT). It also analyzes the mixing time of Markov chains, which is a topic in probability theory and algorithms (cs.DS). The use of noise in the dynamics suggests a connection to reinforcement learning and stochastic optimization (cs.AI). The study of social welfare and long-term behavior of the system suggests a connection to machine learning and decision making (cs.LG). Finally, the analysis of the stationary distribution suggests a connection to statistical inference and modeling (cs.SI).
